her photometrically or using resolved-star\ncolor-magnitude diagrams (CMDs). The important implication for near-field\ncosmology is that star formation histories of comparably massive galaxies\nderived from resolved CMDs should trace the build-up of stellar mass in one\nmain system across cosmic time as opposed to reflecting the contributions of\nmany individual star formation histories of merged dwarfs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 18 Jan 2018 19:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-13"}
