GES vendor-neutral file formats as input files. The\ncomputational cost of the fluid dynamic simulations is further reduced through\nthe application of dynamic mode decomposition to reconstruct the steady state\ntotal drag value given only few initial snapshots of the simulation. The active\nsubspaces analysis is here applied to the geometry of the DTMB-5415 naval\ncombatant hull, which is a common benchmark in ship hydrodynamics simulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 19 Jan 2018 11:21:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 25 Mar 2018 15:08:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-04"}
